name: Dreams, the voices of our unconscious.

metadata.name: The voices of our unconscious
metadata.description:
One Sunday morning at 4 o'clock, Robbie - my cat - decides to wake up and eat his kibble noisily... As I dream, a melody and a scene come to mind.

--

"In the still of night, when slumber reigns supreme,
A feline form awakens from its peaceful dream.
With stealthy steps it creeps, towards its daily feast,
Its soft mews echoing, in a symphony of the least.

The master still lies sleeping, undisturbed by the sound,
But in his dreaming mind, the music can be found.
For every crunch and purr, that the cat does make,
A strange and wondrous melody, in the master's head does wake.

It builds and grows, with each munch of kibble fair,
A concerto of the night, that fills the air.
The beat of pads and whiskers, a rhythm all its own,
A sonata of the cat, that's never heard by dawn.

And when the cat has eaten, and returns to bed,
The master stirs and wonders, what the music he's just heard.
A fleeting dream, a memory, that fades with every light, Of a cat's serenade, in the dead of night."
